Preheat the #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm chips.

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season well with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Cabbage Slaw ==

Halve the @cabbage{1}, cut out and discard the tough core, then thinly slice.

Add the cabbage and @aioli{1%sachet} to a #bowl{} and mix well to combine. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice the @chilli{1} widthways (keeping the seeds and core intact).

In a small bowl, mix the chilli with @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet} and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (double for 4p).

== Sloppy Joe Topping ==

When the potatoes have 10 mins of cooking time left, place a #pan{} over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once the pan is hot, fry the @Irish beef mince{240%g} until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the @Central American style spice mix{2%sachets} to the beef and fry for a further ~{30%seconds}.

Pop in the @tomato paste{1%tin} and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (double for 4p).

Cook for ~{2-3%mins} more. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Once the chips are ready, pop them into an #oven dish{}.

Top with the beef then sprinkle over the @grated cheese{50%g} and @chorizo{100%g}.

Cook on the top shelf of the oven until the cheese is melted, ~{10-15%mins}.

When everything is ready, drizzle the loaded fries with @chipotle paste{2%sachets} and @creme fraiche{110%g}.

Drain the pickled chilli (use less if you don't like spice) and scatter on top of the loaded fries.

Serve the cabbage slaw alongside.